ζυ, the Space between them ZYVNZ, after it is increaſed in the proportion of the Circumference or Radius of the Tropick or Parallel to the Circumference or Radius of the Equator, will give you the meaſure of the Heat upon the Sloping Wall. But this is with neglecting the Effects of the Atmoſphere. Now that Space, or a Solid proportional to it, is found by having the Quadrature and Center of Gravity of the Line of Sines, and of its Segments; all which are already known. The Truth of this Aſſertion is obvious without any farther Demonſtration of it; and will appear to agree with the following Conſtruction, which alſo dos ſolve the Problem.
